@startuml
title Viaverse CI/CD Deployment — Activity Diagram
start
:Merge to protected branch;
:GitHub Actions\ncheckout + cache;
:Run tests\nunit/integration/contract;
:Quality gates\nlint/SAST/dependency scan;
if (Gates pass?) then (yes)
  :Build Docker image;
  :Push to ECR\nimmutable tag;
  :Run Flyway migration\npre-deploy gate;
  :Deploy to EKS\nHelm/Kustomize/GitOps;
  :Smoke tests\nhealth/readiness;
  :Observe metrics/logs\nerror budget;
  if (Healthy?) then (yes)
    :Promote release\nmark version;
  else (no)
    :Rollback\nprevious image/config;
    :Verify rollback health;
  endif
else (no)
  :Fail pipeline\nno deploy;
endif
stop

note bottom
Database migration must be backward-compatible for rolling deploy.
No manual production change without pipeline/audit.
end note
@enduml
